description: Over its 60 year history, Melodifestivalen has had huge success with acts like Abba, Loreen and Mans Zelmerlow.
title: Sweden's Melfest: Why a national Eurovision show won global fans
title_page: Sweden's Melfest: Why a national Eurovision show won global fans - BBC News
maintext: Support for Melfest has grown from outside of Europe, and it was described last week as "the techno version of the primaries" by James Corden during a segment on his US late-night chat show - uploaded to 23 million subscribers on YouTube.
